cuisine: Mediterranean
course: main course
author: HelloFresh
servings: 2
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/shawarma-rama-chicken-kale-salad-63bd8bd87200a0124f00e82a
time required: 35 minutes
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{9%ounce} on a diagonal into ½-inch-thick pieces. Trim, peel, and quarter @shallot{1%unit} lengthwise. Remove and discard any large stems from @kale{4%ounce}; chop into bite-size pieces. Halve @mini cucumber{1%unit} lengthwise; thinly slice into half-moons.

Toss carrots and shallot on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{1%teaspoon}. Season generously with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Meanwhile, place kale in a #large bowl{}; add a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%teaspoon} and a pinch of salt. Using your hands, massage kale (similar to how you would knead dough) until leaves are tender, ~{30-60%seconds}.

Heat a #large dry pan{} over medium heat. Add half the @shawarma spice blend{1%tablespoon} and toast, stirring, until fragrant, ~{30-60%seconds}. Transfer to a #medium bowl{}.

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and season all over with remaining shawarma spice blend, salt, and pepper.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{1%teaspoon} in same pan over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side.

> If chicken begins to brown too quickly, lower heat to medium and cover pan.

Transfer to a #cutting board{}.

While chicken cooks, add @caesar dressing{1.5%ounce}, @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}, half the @white wine vinegar{2%teaspoon}, and 2 TBSP olive oil, and @sugar{1/2%teaspoon} to bowl with toasted shawarma spice blend (use all the vinegar, 4 TBSP olive oil, and 1 tsp sugar for 4 servings). Whisk until smooth; taste and season with salt and pepper.

Slice chicken crosswise.

Add roasted veggies, cucumber, ¾ of the shawarma dressing, and half the @sliced almonds{1/4%ounce} to bowl with kale; toss to combine. Taste and season with salt and pepper.

Divide salad between bowls and top with chicken. Drizzle with remaining shawarma dressing and sprinkle with remaining almonds.

Serve.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.